PERSONALIZED TREATMENT: The range for the maximum number of wrist rotations is 124 ("severe arthritis")-744 ("healthiest individual")
- each stage is incremented by 62 wrist rotations

GENDER
  if female
    lower the max number of wrist rotations/hour by 1 stage
    (women are more likely to experience greater pain from arthritis than men due to 
    a combination of hormonal, biological, and genetic factors)

AGE
  the older a person is
    lower the max number of wrist rotations/hour by 2/year from age 40
    (excess weight increases with age which places larger stress on the joints leading to pain)

TYPE OF ARTHRITIS
  if OA
    lower the max number of wrist rotations/hour by 1 stage
  else if RA
    lower the max number of wrist rotations/hour by 2 stages
  else if RA && OA
    lower the max number of wrist rotations/hour by 3 stages
  else
    do not change max number of wrist rotations/hour

STAGE OF ARTHRITIS
  if stage 1 or no arthritis
    do not change max number of wrist rotations/hour
  else if stage 2
    lower the max number of wrist rotations/hour to 537
  else if stage 3
    lower the max number of wrist rotations/hour to 331
    recommend heat treatment during warm ups to decrease joint inflammation
  else
    recommend the user not to basket weave without consulting a doctor
    lower the max number of wrist rotations/hour to 124

WHAT IS AFFECTED
  if wrist
    lower the max number of wrist rotations/hour
  if fingers
    lower the max number of wrist rotations/hour
    pop ups asking the user if their fingers are in pain
  if hand
    lower the max number of wrist rotations/hour
  if back
    lower the max number of wrist rotations/hour
    remind the user to stand up during break times

CURRENT TREATMENT
  if no
    lower the max number of wrist rotations/hour by 1 stage
